Package: semTests
Type: Package
Title: Robust Test Statistics for Structural Equation Models
Description: Supports penalized eigenvalue block-averaging and penalized
    regression p-values (Foldnes, Moss, Grønneberg, 2025)
    <doi:10.1080/10705511.2024.2372028>, including their extension to nested
    model comparison (Foldnes, Grønneberg, Moss, 2026)
    <doi:10.3758/s13428-026-02968-4>, as well as traditional p-values such as
    Satorra-Bentler. For classical continuous, complete-data maximum likelihood,
    variants can use biased or unbiased gamma estimates (Du, Bentler, 2022)
    <doi:10.1080/10705511.2022.2063870> and either the standard or reweighted
    least-squares statistic. The weighted chi-square framework also supports
    minimum-discrepancy GLS, ULS, and categorical DWLS/ULS/WLS families, with
    experimental implementation support for non-ML estimators, categorical
    nested comparison, categorical pairwise missingness, and full-information
    maximum-likelihood (FIML) fits under missing data.
Version: 0.9.0
